The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Phone restore plan
                                                                                                               Phone restore plan
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	At least half the telephone and Internet connections to hospitals, banks and police and BSF installations affected in Tuesday nights fire at Circus Exchange are expected to be restored by Friday afternoon, said BSNL officials on Thursday.         
	Residential phone lines will take longer to restore.        
	Telephone connections to chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjees house and Tata Centre are expected be restored on Friday morning.        
	We are working round the clock to restore all the affected connections within seven days, as we had promised, said an official of Calcutta Telephones.                                                                                                                                                                            
